summaries.overall_summary: Mr Ramlal has called the ITC customer service several times regarding issues with his order, but his issues have not been resolved. He is frustrated and would like a status update. The customer service representative, Monika, checks his record and informs him that there are three complaints against his order. Ramlal informs her that he did not receive the goods and that the delivery person claimed that he did not receive the goods either. Ramlal also mentions that he was overcharged for a fever medicine. Monika offers him a replacement, but Ramlal wants a refund instead. Monika checks the status of his complaint and informs him that it has been escalated to the next level of support. She asks him to provide his contact information so that someone can reach out to him soon. Ramlal provides his phone number and email address, and the call ends with Monika assuring him that someone will contact him shortly.
summaries.speaker_a_summary: Mr Ramlal is calling about issues he has had with receiving proper customer service and having his complaints resolved. Monika, whose team he was speaking with, was not there to take his call and he was passed on to another representative. They check his complaints and inform him that some have been resolved but others still need attention. They apologize for lack of service and promise to prioritize his issues and have someone address them as soon as possible.
summaries.speaker_b_summary: Monika calls Ramal madam to inform her that she hasn't spoken to Sana and hasn't received any goods from her. Monika denies buying a receiver from Ajay or having the goods and receiver he sent. She is frustrated with the situation and would like an update from Ramal madam. She is also frustrated that her team writes things without her knowledge, and she has to clean up the mess. Monika gives madam the complaint number and the phone number Amit had given her. She also informs her that Amit's number has changed. Madam is not satisfied with the information provided and asks Monika to figure out the issue. Monika suggests involving Sharad to resolve the situation.
summaries.cohere_points:
- Monika from ITC calls a customer, Ramal, as per his request to address his grievances that have not been resolved yet.
- Ramal was on vacation and couldn't be reached by their employees, so his complaints accumulated.
- Monika transfers him to different departments during the call, but none of the issues get resolved.
- The call ends without any resolution and Monika promises to look into the issue despite knowing that it will not make any difference. 
- Throughout the call, the customer is very frustrated and complains about the lack of help from the company.
